[Name] Tcpdump
[Summary] A tool for network monitoring and data acquisition.
[License] BSD License (original)
[Description] Tcpdump allows you to dump the traffic on a network. It can be used to print out the headers of packets on a network interface that matches a given expression. You can use this tool to track down network problems, to detect "ping attacks" or to monitor the network activities.
[Homepage] http://www.tcpdump.org/
